<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54005b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54005b">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54005b"> 5(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> houdah / mahout / keddah / trunk in mouth </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: HOUDAH (Arabic <i>houdaj</i>, a litter carried by an elephant, or a camel), a seat to contain two or more persons, usually fitted with a railing and a canopy, erected on the back of an elephant. <br>MAHOUT (Hind. <i>mahawat</i>), an elephant-driver. The mahout sits on the elephant&apos;s neck and directs him by voice and by the use of a goad called <i>anhus</i>. <br>KEDDAH (from Hindu <i>Khedna</i>, to chase), the term used in India for the enclosure constructed to entrap elephants. </mm> </dd></dl>
